==English==

===Etymology===
* From {{L.}} ''[[candidatus]]'' meaning "a person who is standing for public office", the perfect passive participle of the verb ''[[candidare]]'', which in turn comes from ''candidus'' meaning "candid" or "white", in reference to Roman candidates wearing bleached white togas as a symbol of purity at a public forum.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[person]] who is [[run]]ning in an [[election]] or who is [[apply]]ing to a [[position]] for a [[job]].
# A [[participant]] in an [[examination]].

